 $\\mathrm{FP}_{1}^{\\pm}$,\n$\\mathrm{FP}_{2}^{\\pm}$, and $\\mathrm{FP}_{3}^{\\pm}$, respectively. Rather, QSH\nbecomes anisotropic nearby $\\mathrm{FP}_{41,42,43}^{\\pm}$ with one component\nleading and the others subleading. Besides, Nem.site(bond), chiral\nsuperconductivity, and nematic-spin-nematic (NSN.) site(bond) are subleading\ncandidates around these FPs.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 1 May 2023 04:11:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-05-02"}
